# Auto deploy (revzio website)

After completing any code/content change in this repo:

1. **Commit and push automatically** — do not ask the user for permission first.
2. Push to `origin main` on `puneet-revzio/website` when the task is done (or at a natural checkpoint for multi-step work).
3. Use SSH remote (`git@github.com:puneet-revzio/website.git`) if HTTPS auth fails.
4. Follow the existing commit message style: concise, why-focused, complete sentences.
5. **Do not commit** junk or accidental files: `.DS_Store`, misplaced duplicates under `js/*.css`, root-level stray SVGs, credentials, or `.env`.
6. Only include untracked files when they are clearly part of the requested change (e.g. new assets under `assets/`).

Vercel deploys from `main` — pushing is how changes go live.
